        <abstract> 
<p>JS is proposing to write a detailed history of the polled Aberdeen breed of cattle [James Macdonald and James Sinclair, <hi rend="italic">History of polled Aberdeen or Angus cattle</hi> (1882)] and would be grateful for any instances of hornless breeds known to CD; in particular asks his opinion on the cause of the peculiarity.</p> 
